NO SOLICITATIONS<br>
Premier Lake Tahoe private community is seeking an experienced leader to join our team as Executive Chef. <br>
Martis Camp Club is the premier private club in the Lake Tahoe area and is looking to be recognized as one of the best four season, year round mountain club and communities in the western United States. It requires an Executive Chef who can contribute leadership, professionalism, positive energy, contagious enthusiasm, depth of knowledge and hands on participation to his/her TEAM in a private club environment with the expectation to be known for its innovative culinary concepts and delivery. In short, focused on consistency, creativity, variety and quality.<br>
<br>
POSITION SUMMARY<br>
The Executive Chef will operate within the boundaries of the yearly schedule, budge and Club Rules, under the direction of the Food and Beverage Director, and in accordance with the Club Vision, Mission, Goals and service standards. Experience in developing creative menu concepts is essential. The Executive Chef will supervise 3 Chef de Cuisines (1 at the Camp Lodge, 1 at the Family Barn, 1 at the Lookout Lodge) and a Pastry Chef while overseeing the culinary operations at the Camp Lodge, Family Barn, Lookout Lodge, golf snack bar, locker rooms, Beach Shack, and special events (weddings, golf events, concert barbecues, banquets). In total, there are approximately 20 culinary Ambassadors at peak times, which include stewards.<br>
The Executive Chef will plan, budget, approve menus, and staff and oversee all culinary venues to the highest standard of culinary expression. The Executive Chef will communicate actively with other department heads on the events and activities of the Club. This Executive Chef will be hands on, leading, mentoring all culinary Ambassadors in all Food and Beverage venues, and will visit all venues frequently to guide, assist, and ensure quality standards and presentations. Martis Camp Club is peak on weekends and holidays in the summer and winter months, which will require additional attention to service and staffing levels during these times.<br>
<br>
Plan, manage and provide a unique culinary experience at:<br>
-The Camp Lodge with an emphasis on a cliff room (elegant) dining menu that varies weekly, creative culinary expression, meticulous preparation and presentation, and a bar/bistro menu that reflects the casual nature of the environment. Floor time is suggested on a nightly basis. This also includes outlets in the men's and ladies locker rooms and spa with appropriate, casual and light menu selections. Expedite the Camp Lodge wine dinners and elegant dinners when offered for evening service.<br>
-The Family Barn that fulfills the Soda Fountain concept of family, fun, healthy and delicious food.<br>
-The Lookout Lodge with the quality of culinary expression of comfort food which is offered in a set summer and winter environment.<br>
-The Beach Shack with an emphasis on light, summer offerings in an environment on the Lake.<br>
<br>
Duties include:<br>
 ·         Accommodate Club and member wishes and desires for wedding, concert barbecues, banquet functions, golf events and other member outings.<br>
·         Assist the Food and Beverage Director in the preparation and adherence of both the Food and Beverage annual operational and capital budgets, including menu costing and pricing.<br>
·         Exhibit professional behavior in actions and attire, with BOH and FOH staff members. Establish a positive, TEAM environment within the culinary staffing so that staff members will be supported and respected in the work environment and valued for their contributions.<br>
·         Develop written spec sheets for each menu item to include; name, description, portion size, ingredients, cost per serving and menu price. Also responsible for taking pictures of all menu items and for maintaining both the photos and spec sheets in a central location. (This is for the on-going training of staff, to serve as a reference for the special dietary needs of guests' and to insure the consistency in both menu preparation and presentation).<br>
·         Prepare and work within an annual budget, with monthly variance review, assisted by the Food and Beverage Director, including annual projections and future F&B concepts for refinements and future consideration.<br>
·         Plan, schedule, coordinate, and communicate all culinary meetings on a regular, mandatory and consistent basis.<br>
·         Establish and manage internal cost and labor controls.<br>
·         Is actively involved in the daily operation by being a "hands on" Chef through modeling proper culinary techniques and working alongside employees. Exhibit a professional demeanor through appearance and by maintaining a positive attitude toward all Ambassadors and guests.<br>
·         Be mindful of the health and wellness component of the Club, which will focus on the spiritual, emotional, mental and physical wellbeing of Club members.<br>
·         Coordinate staffing levels and food preparation daily to ensure the timing and flow of food service meets the demands of the membership.<br>
·         Promote an organic, fresh and healthy culinary expression in ALL culinary expressions.<br>
·         Establish and maintain all par levels for food items, kitchen supplies and all other necessary products needed to operate the culinary department.<br>
·         Responsible for maintaining clean and organized storage areas for all food items and for proper rotation.<br>
·         Oversee the compliance of state health regulations in the safe handling, storage and service of all food items. Also responsible for ensuring that all china, glassware, silver and kitchen equipment is properly sanitized, racked and/or stored.<br>
·         Develops strong working relationships with other Department Managers to ensure communication and teamwork is at an optimum.<br>
·         Other duties may be assigned <br>
<br>
SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES:<br>
Chef de Cuisine (3), Pastry Chef (1), and an additional 24 culinary ambassadors throughout all outlets. The Executive Chef is responsible for the overall direction, coordination, evaluation, culinary expression and menu offerings for each kitchen. The Executive Chef will carry out management responsibilities in accordance with the organization's policies and applicable Federal and State Laws. Responsibilities include planning, assigning and directing work, appraising performance, rewarding and disciplining employees, addressing complaints and resolving problems.<br>
<br>
ALL EMPLOYEES ARE REQUIRED TO SUBMIT AND PASS A DRUG TEST PRIOR TO EMPLOYMENT. CONSUMPTION OF ALCOHOL IS NOT ALLOWED ON CLUB GROUNDS. EMPLOYMENT IS "AT WILL".<br>
<br>
REQUIREMENTS<br>
Must have Executive Level work experience as an Executive Chef in Fine Dining<br>
Must have previously managed at least 20 subordinates and managed a large budget<br>
Must have leadership knowledge, techniques, and education<br>
<br>
COMPENSATION<br>
Full time, year round position<br>
 Compensation package is based on qualifications and experience.<br>
 This position does not accrue PTO, but would expect 12 days of paid vacation. Vacation time to be taken during non-peak times of year.<br>
 One week of continuing education or new restaurant exposure annually.<br>
 Expense reimbursement for education, reference trips and professional growth, to be taken and used during spring and fall periods.<br>
 Health, dental, vision, and life insurance for yourself with monthly employee participation.<br>
 Company cell phone and computer.<br>
 Fitness Bonus<br>
 Uniform allowance<br>
 401 (k) with 100% match up to 7% of compensation. <br>
<br>
Tagged as: elevated banquet cuisine, fine dining, high end bar bistro, high paced upscale comfort food<br>
Salary: $76-100,000 (Annual)<br>
<br>
Email cover letter and resume to: HR@MartisCamp.com<br>
**NO PHONE CALLS PLEASE**NO SOLICITATIONS    </section>

